      • getPathSize

        public static long getPathSize(org.apache.hadoop.fs.FileSystem fs,
               org.apache.hadoop.fs.Path path)
                        throws IOException
        Get the actual size of all data in the given directory. If the input is a single file, its size is returned immediately. If the input is a directory, we returns the total size of all data in that directory. If there is a global index, the size is retrieved from that global index. Otherwise, we add up all the sizes of single files.
        Parameters:
        fs - - the file system that contains the path
        path - - the path that contains the data
        Returns:
        Throws:
        IOException
